    {
      "text": "Esper Dream (エスパードリーム, Esupā Dorīmu) is an action role-playing video game developed and published by Konami for the Family Computer Disk System. It was released in Japan on February 20, 1987.  During this time, RPGs had a particular look and feel, primarily utilizing sword and magic motifs.  Esper Dream takes place instead in a fairy tale world featuring a young boy with ESP talents who wields a gun.\nA sequel, Esper Dream 2: Aratanaru Tatakai (エスパードリーム2 新(あら)たなる戦(たたか)い, lit. \"Esper Dream 2: New Battle), was released for the Family Computer on June 26, 1992.",
      "lang": "en",
      "source": "wikipedia_en"
    }
